<br>
Over the weekend, I tried to make an Imbued Elven Chain Mantle (using a Fire Opal).  I tried the following , but it didn't work (ie was not a valid recipe):<br>
<br>
1 Chainmail mantle pattern<br>
2 Enchanted Mithril Rings<br>
1 Silk Swatch<br>
1 Imbued Fire Opal<br>
1 Moonlight Temper<br>
1 Elven Smithy Hammer<br>
<br>
Luckily, items do not seem to be consumed on invalid recipes using a Koada'Dal Forge.  Because of this I was able to try different variations on the original recipe. I'm not sure if the other cultural forges work this way, but I'd like to know.<br>
<br>
If ANYONE can shed some light on this I'd be very grateful.  Is this the way imbued recipes normally work?  Is it impossible to make Solusek Ro (hence the Fire Opal) imbued mithril?  Is it impossible to imbue chain mantles? Are the recipes bugged?  Etc...<br>
<br>
Or even, is there an NPC that tells you how and what can be imbued with Fire Opals?  I tried the temple of Solusek Ro, but didn't find anything.<br>
<br>
In the end, I pulled the Fire Opal out of the recipe and made an Enchanted Elven Chain Mantle.  2 int, 2 wis, 2sv magic, 6 AC, and weighs 0.7 stone wearable by all light elves and their associated classes.  It's a decent item, but I'd much prefer something imbued.<br>
<br>
Thanks for reading <p> 
