<br>
To Pgrinsell:<br>
I highly suggest you look for recipes in game, and &quot;wing it&quot;.  I had SO MUCH FUN working on my mantle.  Sure it's not the greatest stats (2 int 2 wis and 2 sv magic) but it's decent if you need them.  You only lose your smithing components in a Koada'Dal Forge if they can create an item.  If you get an incorrect recipe, you can open the forge after hitting combine to get your components back.  I assume all the other <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> cultural</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> forges work the same way. <p> 
